# UI/UX Principles for Non-Technical Users

Since this application targets non-technical poultry farmers, all UI development should follow these principles: This is purely mobile friendly application.

## Simplicity

- Use clear, simple language (avoid technical jargon)
- Minimize the number of steps to complete tasks
- Provide obvious navigation paths
- Use progressive disclosure for advanced features

## Intuitive Design

- Follow familiar UI patterns (forms, tables, dashboards)
- Use consistent layouts across the application
- Provide meaningful feedback for actions
- Use visual cues and icons to enhance understanding

## Error Prevention & Recovery

- Validate inputs as early as possible
- Provide clear error messages in simple language
- Offer guidance on how to fix issues
- Include fallback options for when features fail

## Accessibility

- Support various screen sizes (responsive design)
- Ensure adequate color contrast
- Provide text alternatives for non-text content
- Support keyboard navigation

## Performance

- Minimize loading times and data fetching
- Provide visual feedback during longer operations
- Cache frequently accessed data
- Implement offline functionality where possible

## Technology

- Nextjs with ShadCN and TailwindCSS